Source: Weeds of New Zealand
Author: HILGENDORF
Vol / Page: 152
Edition: 1967
Quote: BLACK NIGHTSHADE (<i>Solanum nigrum</i>), is called also white nightshade, mother-of-thousands, black tomato, black potato, wonder berry, and by a serious confusion deadly nightshade and bittersweet. Increasingly common from Auckland southward to Otago.
